---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import BrandArchitectureDiagram from '../../components/BrandArchitectureDiagram.astro';

const builtWith = [
  'Field-specific educators',
  'Appropriate professional standards',
  'Documented learning objectives',
  'Programme governance',
  'Assessment principles',
  'Ethical communication',
  'Faculty documentation',
  'Review and update cycles',
  'Transparent certificate criteria',
  'Professional relevance',
];

const futureFieldGroups = [
  {
    title: 'Clinical & Health Sciences',
    fields: ['Medicine', 'Dentistry', 'Pharmacy', 'Health Sciences'],
  },
  {
    title: 'Practice, Society & Business',
    fields: ['Law', 'Business & Leadership', 'Practice & Institutional Management', 'Professional Communication'],
  },
  {
    title: 'Emerging Fields',
    fields: ['Artificial Intelligence & Digital Transformation', 'Technology'],
  },
];

const sharedStandards = [
  'Defined learning objectives',
  'Structured modules and assessments',
  'Documented faculty profiles',
  'Evidence-informed content',
  'Versioned references and review cycles',
  'Transparent certificate criteria',
  'Ethical communication',
  'Professional relevance',
  'Responsible use of emerging technologies, including AI where applicable',
];

const collaborationTypes = [
  'Academic review',
  'Faculty collaboration',
  'Programme co-development',
  'Future academy development',
  'Institutional partnership',
  'Professional association collaboration',
];
---
<Base
  title="Professional Academies · Academia Europa"
  description="Academia Europa is the institutional home for specialised professional academies. One institution, multiple fields of professional mastery, beginning with Veterinary Academy International."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Professional Academies"
    title="One institution. Multiple fields of professional mastery."
    lede="Academia Europa is designed as the institutional home for specialised professional academies. Each academy focuses on a defined professional field while sharing a common framework of structured learning, academic documentation, ethical communication, and professional relevance."
  />

  <Section eyebrow="The Academy Model" title="Field-led. Institutionally governed.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>Each academy under Academia Europa is developed around the needs of a specific professional field. Subject expertise is field-led, while the educational framework is supported by Academia Europa's standards for programme design, learning objectives, assessment, evidence-informed content, faculty documentation, and review cycles.</p>
      <p>The result is intended to be a credible institution within each field, supported by a shared academic discipline that travels with the institution as it grows.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Architecture" tone="ivory">
    <BrandArchitectureDiagram />
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="How Our Academies Are Built" title="Built deliberately, not assembled.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl mb-10">
      <p>Future academies are not built as collections of unrelated courses. Each is developed with field-specific educators, appropriate professional standards, and the institutional architecture, academic discipline, and quality framework that Academia Europa provides.</p>
    </div>
    <ul class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 max-w-3xl">
      {builtWith.map((b) => (
        <li class="flex gap-3 items-baseline text-graphite leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-champagne text-xs">—</span><span>{b}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Current Specialised Academy" title="Veterinary Academy International." tone="ivory">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl">
      <p>Veterinary Academy International is the first specialised academy of Academia Europa, dedicated to structured postgraduate veterinary education and professional development.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/academies/vai" class="btn">Discover VAI</a>
        <a href="https://vai.vet" rel="noopener" class="btn">Visit VAI</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Future Academy Fields" title="A multi-disciplinary trajectory.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl mb-12">
      <p>Academia Europa is designed to expand into additional professional fields where structured postgraduate learning, ethical education, and professional mastery are needed. The institutional framework remains constant; the academies are field-led.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 max-w-5xl">
      {futureFieldGroups.map((g) => (
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow mb-5">{g.title}</div>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {g.fields.map((f) => (
              <li class="font-serif text-lg text-navy-deep border-t border-platinum pt-3">{f}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
    <p class="mt-10 text-sm text-muted max-w-3xl">…and other specialised professional fields, developed as the institution and its partners identify need.</p>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="A Future-Facing Direction" title="Artificial Intelligence & Digital Transformation." tone="ivory">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="md:col-span-7 prose-editorial">
        <p>Artificial intelligence is becoming part of professional practice across healthcare, law, business, education, clinical decision-making, and institutional management. Academia Europa's future academy architecture may include AI-focused education that helps professionals understand, evaluate, and apply emerging technologies responsibly within their field.</p>
        <p>Our position is academic, not promotional. AI education within Academia Europa should focus not on trend-following, but on responsible professional application: understanding tools, evaluating evidence, managing risk, and integrating digital transformation ethically into practice.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-5 border-l border-champagne pl-8 py-2">
        <div class="eyebrow mb-3">Editorial Principle</div>
        <blockquote class="font-serif italic text-xl md:text-2xl text-navy-deep leading-snug">
          "Professional education about AI should teach judgement, not enthusiasm."
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Shared Institutional Standards" title="What every academy shares.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl mb-10">
      <p>Although each academy serves a different professional field, all academies developed under Academia Europa are intended to share a common academic foundation: structured programme design, defined learning outcomes, ethical communication, transparent certificate criteria, and a commitment to professional relevance.</p>
    </div>
    <ul class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 max-w-3xl">
      {sharedStandards.map((s) => (
        <li class="flex gap-3 items-baseline text-graphite leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-champagne text-xs">—</span><span>{s}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Collaborate on a Future Academy" title="Open to educators, institutions, and professional bodies." tone="ivory">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-3xl mb-10">
      <p>Academia Europa welcomes dialogue with educators, institutions, professional bodies, and experienced practitioners interested in developing structured postgraduate learning in specialised fields.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 max-w-3xl mb-10">
      {collaborationTypes.map((c) => (
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-baseline text-graphite leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-champagne text-xs">—</span><span>{c}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a href="/partnerships" class="btn">Partnerships & Academic Review</a>
      <a href="mailto:academic@academiaeuropa.com" class="btn">Email the Academic Office</a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Base>
